Secretory otitis media: a review of management by consultant otolaryngologists.
 A questionnaire concerning various aspects of secretory otitis media was completed by a random sample of Consultant Otolaryngologists in the United Kingdom.
 The replies to questions associated with the management of this condition are presented.
 The results suggest only a moderate degree of agreement between Consultants in many areas of management and these findings are discussed in the light of current research.
